race.comment: DARKNCONFIDENTIAL (2) made an encouraging return here last week, closing strongly into the placings off a soft tempo. He'll relish the rise in trip and should be storming home again. KOMACHI (3) is humming along and was only denied narrowly in the Strathalbyn Cup six days ago. He gets a handy weight swing and is a three-time winner at this track. Major threat. CRIMSON VINE (7) returned to something like her best at Murray Bridge, launching late to score over this trip. She strips fitter and stays in low at the weights. Can keep the ball rolling. ARUGAMAMA (1) is capable on her day but can be tricky to catch. Three hitouts in readiness should have her forward enough. SENTIMENTAL FLAME (10) has figures that stack up and is worth keeping safe.
